added.title: Lucky Stars
added.description: Raven explains astrology to the Titans and tells their horoscopes, but Cyborg does not believe.

added.title: Various Modes of Transportation
added.description: With the other Titans away, Cyborg is forced to take a road trip with Robin.

added.title: Winter Break
added.description: Craig returns to the Creek after the long Winter Break only to find an empty wasteland and danger lurking in the snow.

added.title: Snack to the Future
added.description: Owen wants his favorite treat, Jiggle Giggle, so bad that he's willing to use a time machine to get to snacktime quicker. But when he ends up stuck in the past, Owen must decide between getting home and getting fed.

added.title: The Gold and the Stickerful
added.description: Courtney becomes infatuated with a new gold sticker incentive program that Chef introduces to the class.

added.title: Simons Are Forever
added.description: Duncan and Leshawna try to take advantage of Izzy's love for the game of Simon Says.

added.title: Stop! Hamster Time
added.description: Owen takes over the job of caring for the class hamster and learns that he's evil.

added.title: Driving Miss Crazy
added.description: Duncan leads Beth to believe she's broken his battery-powered bike and makes her chauffeur him around in a wagon for the day as punishment.

added.title: #Frenemies Part 1
added.description: Batgirl's worlds collide when her best friend from Gotham City moves to Metropolis. Meanwhile, Catwoman is making some new friends of her own.

added.title: #Frenemies Part 2
added.description: Batgirl's worlds collide when her best friend from Gotham City moves to Metropolis. Meanwhile, Catwoman is making some new friends of her own.

added.title: Game Over
added.description: Unagami breaks into the real world and terrorizes Ninjago City while Jay, Zane and Pixal attempt to prevent disaster by reuniting Unagami with his creator, Milton Dyer.

added.title: Shintaro
added.description: The ninja are invited to attend the birthday party of Princess Vania, in the distant Kingdom of Shintaro. They depart, bringing along Master Wu, unaware that he is feeling his age…

added.title: Into the Dark
added.description: When Cole investigates a mysterious visitor, the ninja aren't sure what to believe. Cole is frustrated with this lack of team support, until Princess Vania reveals a secret entrance that leads to an underground mine beneath Shintaro - where the city's dark secrets are held.

added.title: The Worst Rescue Ever
added.description: The ninja attempt to rescue Cole, but the bickering of his fellow prisoners, the Geckles and Munce, alerts the Skull Sorcerer, and soon the ninja are prisoners too.

added.title: The Two Blades
added.description: In order to escape the Skull Sorcerer's chain-gang, the ninja must convince the Munce and Geckles to put aside their distrust and work together… by promising them something they may not be able to deliver -- The Blades of Deliverance!

added.title: Mumm-Ra, the Ever-Living
added.description: Every time Mumm-Ra gets a hold of a magic artifact to restore his powers, the ThunderCats just smash it and turn him into a dinky skeleton again. Until today that is, because Mumm-Ra just remembered he's got the Ancient Spirits of Evil, and now he can get swole whenever he wants!

added.title: Berserkers
added.description: The Cats' Lair is attacked by gold-loving robot pirates, the Berserkers! This is a good thing, really, since it means Lion-O and the ThunderKittens can ditch their chores and fight robo-pirates instead! Just don't tell Tygra!!!!

added.title: Jaga History
added.description: Freed from the Astral Plane, Jaga, ghost of the ThunderCats mentor, is now free to visit the Cats' Lair. Which means he can finally tell them why Thundera, their home world, exploded. It's story time!

added.title: Barbastella
added.description: While flying with his new invention, Panthro hits it off with a new friend, Barbastella, the Queen of the Bats! Now Panthro needs help getting ready for his big date with her, because it turns out Panthro is terrified of bats! Lion-O and Cheetara are happy to help but, wow, that is a lot to unpack.

added.title: Adopt a Jackal
added.description: After a battle with the Mutants, Jackalman gets confused and accidentally returns to the Cats' Lair with the Thundercats, he is the dumbest mutant. Jackalman pretends to be a Thundercat so his enemies won't catch him and the Thundercats pretend to play along because they feel bad for him!

added.title: Bear-Knuckle Brawl
added.description: Axel must team up with Bearbarian to stop Madcap from transforming Luka's stuffed bear collection into an invincible army.

added.title: Saving Private Masko
added.description: Masko takes Axel's call for more discipline too seriously and loses sight of his own identity in the process, becoming a no-nonsense soldier set on toeing the line - and ill-equipped for a lucha libre with Madcap!

added.title: Unfriendly Competition
added.description: Aki must set aside a petty rivalry with Bert Wily in order to stop Chemistry Man from wreaking havoc at Silicon Central's Field Day.

added.title: Opposites Attract
added.description: Fire Man and Wave Man team up to evaporate the city's water supply, forcing Mega Man to team up with an ally of his own- Suna.

added.title: I.C.E. (In Case of Emergency)
added.description: When Ice Man decides to be a hero, Mega Man, influenced by Ice Man's literalness, steps down from the hero biz until a true crisis snaps him out of it.

added.title: Trust Your Guts, Man!
added.description: Guts Man tries to undo Dr. Light's eco-friendly disposal of trash in Silicon City by infiltrating the family and destroying the Lighthouse so he can eat it!

added.title: Drill of the Hunt
added.description: Mega Man tries a quick fix using Hypno Woman's powers to rehabilitate Drill Man, to disastrous results!

added.title: Two Lies, One Truth
added.description: As Lloyd unmasks Mystake for who she truly is, Emperor Garmadon embraces Harumi as his daughter of darkness. Meanwhile, Wu holds onto faith as he leads his friends into dangerous Oni territory in the hope of finding Firstbourne's nest

added.title: The Weakest Link
added.description: Lloyd turns the tables on Harumi to take his father's power away, and the Ninja learn what it takes to be a Dragon Hunter.

added.title: Saving Faith
added.description: Lloyd and his team plot to take control of the Oni Titan. Meanwhile in the First Realm, the Ninja fall into Iron Baron's clutches and an old master returns.

added.title: Lessons for a Master
added.description: When Iron Baron forces Wu to retrieve the Dragon Armor, things don't go as planned. In Ninjago, Lloyd can only endure so much as he holds onto hope for the Ninjas' return.

added.title: Green Destiny
added.description: The Ninja finally return home and unite to stop Emperor Garmadon, forcing Lloyd to make a decision that will forever change Ninjago.

added.title: Journey to the Valley of Repugnus Part 1
added.description: Bumblebee and Grimlock are separated as they search the depths of Cybertron for another of Windblade's psychic shards, encountering the Monsterbots and the Energon Masters.

added.title: Journey to the Valley of Repugnus Part 2
added.description: Bee and Grimlock navigate the strange cultures of the Energon Masters and Monsterbots, uncovering a shocking secret about the two seemingly-different peoples.

added.title: Rack N' Ruin N' Ratchet Part 1
added.description: Rack'N'Ruin join Ratchet on a rescue mission to save Jetfire, who has gone down behind enemy lines.

added.title: Rack N' Ruin N' Ratchet Part 2
added.description: Rack'N'Ruin must rescue the rescue mission when Astrotrain and Dead End kidnap Jetfire and Ratchet.

added.title: Dweller in the Depths Part 1
added.description: When a mysterious shark-bot named Hammerbyte kidnaps comatose Windblade, Bee and Chromia must chase him into the depths of the Argon Sea to retrieve her.

added.title: Dweller in the Depths Part 2
added.description: Optimus receives a dire warning from the Primes as Chromia and Bee pursue Windblade into a waking Titan under the sea.

added.title: Dos mentiras una verdad
added.description: Cuando Lloyd desenmascara y revela la identidad de Mystake, el Emperador Garmadon acepta a Harumi como su hija de la oscuridad. Mientras tanto, Wu se aferra a su fe al llevar a sus amigos hacia territorios Oni peligrosos esperando encontrar el nido de la Primogénita.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: El eslabon mas debil
added.description: Lloyd le paga con la misma moneda a Harumi para quitarle el poder a su padre, y los Ninjas aprenden lo que se necesita para ser un Cazador de Dragones.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Salvando a Faith
added.description: Lloyd y su equipo planean tomar el control del Oni Titan. Mientras tanto en el Primer Reino, los Ninja caen en las garras del Barón de Hierro y un viejo maestro regresa.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Lecciones para un maestro
added.description: Cuando el Barón de Hierro obliga a Wu a tomar la Armadura de Dragón, las cosas no salen como se planearon. En Ninjago, hay un límite de lo que Lloyd puede soportar mientras se aferra a la esperanza del regreso de los Ninjas.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Destino verde
added.description: Los Ninjas regresan por fin a casa y se unen para detener al Emperador Garmadon, obligando a Lloyd a tomar una decisión que cambiará por siempre a Ninjago.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Mumm-Ra, el Inmortal
added.description: Cada vez que Mumm-Ra se hace con un artefacto mágico para restablecer sus poderes, los ThunderCats lo destrozan y vuelven a convertirlo en un esqueleto. Hasta hoy, porque Mumm-Ra acaba de recordar que cuenta con los Antiguos Espíritus del Mal, y ahora, podrá ponerse fuerte siempre que quiera.

added.title: Simon por siempre
added.description: Duncan y Leshawna tratan de aprovecharse del amor de Izzy por el juego de Simón Dice.

added.title: #AmiEnemigas - Segunda Parte
added.description: Los mundos de Batgirl colisionan cuando su mejor amiga de Gotham City se muda a Metrópolis. Mientras tanto, Catwoman también hace nuevos amigos...
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: Pelea de Nudillos de Oso
added.description: Axel debe formar equipo con Bearbarian para evitar que Madcap transforme la colección de osos de peluche de Luka en un ejército invencible.

added.title: La super moto
added.description: Duncan hace que Beth crea que rompió su bicicleta impulsada a batería y hace que lo lleve de un lugar a otro en su carrito todo el día como castigo.

added.title: El dia del hamster
added.description: Owen toma el trabajo de cuidar al hamster de la clase y descubre que es malvado.

added.title: Salvar al Soldado Masko
added.description: Masko toma demasiado en serio el llamado de Axel para una mayor disciplina y pierde de vista su propia identidad en el proceso, convirtiéndose en un soldado sin sentido dispuesto a seguir la línea, iy mal equipado para una lucha libre con Madcap!

added.title: #AmiEnemigas - Primera Parte
added.description: Los mundos de Batgirl colisionan cuando su mejor amiga de Gotham City se muda a Metrópolis. Mientras tanto, Catwoman también hace nuevos amigos…
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol
